  "_doc": "Phase-3c demo: 2:1 and 4:1 multiplexers side by side. Click VERILOG in the bottom toolbar to see how they lower:\n  • The 2:1 MUX uses a clean ternary: `assign y2 = sel ? d1 : d0;`\n  • The 4:1 MUX builds a 2-bit select via concat (`{s1, s0}`) and a nested-ternary chain that reads cleanly: `(({s1,s0}==2'h0) ? e0 : (...==2'h1) ? e1 : (...==2'h2) ? e2 : e3)`.\nBoth forms are synthesisable and parse cleanly with iverilog. Wider muxes follow the same pattern; the next substep will add `case`-based emission via IRAlways for designs that prefer it.",
